/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201635/Ibis-Exie-Pajaro-Manufacturing-9-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201635/Ibis-Exie-Pajaro-Manufacturing-9-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201635/Ibis-Exie-Pajaro-Manufacturing-9-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201635/Ibis-Exie-Pajaro-Manufacturing-9-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201635/Ibis-Exie-Pajaro-Manufacturing-9-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><figure id=\"attachment_263697\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-263697\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1.jpg\" alt=\"New carbon manufacturing facility for Ibis in Pajaro for Ibis Exie \" width=\"1228\" height=\"655\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1.jpg 1228w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-297x158.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-800x427.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-120x64.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-768x410.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-696x371.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-1068x570.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-787x420.jpg 787w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1228px) 100vw, 1228px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1.jpg 1228w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-297x158.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-800x427.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-120x64.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-768x410.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-696x371.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-1068x570.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202010/Ibis-Exie-pajaro-manufacturing-1-787x420.jpg 787w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-263697\">The new Ibis carbon manufacturing facility is in Pajaro, CA, which is about 30 minutes from Santa Cruz. Note the full solar array on the roof.</figcaption></figure><p>Ibis also points out that the molds are internally heated which makes them more energy efficient – enough so that they can power the process with their own solar panels on the factory roof. All of this results in fewer hours spent building each frame, and less energy used to manufacture them, all while offsetting the energy needed to build the frames through renewable sources.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab.jpg\" alt=\"Ibis Exie carbon frame test facility\" width=\"1084\" height=\"662\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab.jpg 1084w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-297x181.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-800x489.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-120x73.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-768x469.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-696x425.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-1068x652.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-688x420.jpg 688w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1084px) 100vw, 1084px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab.jpg 1084w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-297x181.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-800x489.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-120x73.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-768x469.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-696x425.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-1068x652.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30202016/Ibis-test-lab-688x420.jpg 688w\"></a></p><p>Hans goes on to say that they’ve invested in their own testing facility so that they can go back and forth between prototyping and testing quickly. That has given them the opportunity to do more iterations of each prototype, making lighter and stronger parts.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30190641/Ibis-Exie-Pajaro-Manufacturing-XC-mountain-bike-carbon-made-in-USA-651.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30190641/Ibis-Exie-Pajaro-Manufacturing-XC-mountain-bike-carbon-made-in-USA-651.jpg\" alt=\"Made in the USA Ibis Exie carbon mountain bike with build team \" width=\"1600\" height=\"1066\" data-ezsrcset=\"https: