/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30201619/Chip-Shreds-9-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Want one? Like all bikes at the moment, the big question mark is the supply chain needed for Ibis to spec the bikes. They’re hoping to have complete bikes rolling out the door this summer. But because of the uncertainty with what will be available, when, they’re saying that builds are subject to change.</p><p>But we can tell you that pricing for complete bikes will start around $7,999 and top out somewhere around $12,799. The frame only will also be offered for $4,499 which includes a 7 year warranty on the frame and lifetime replacement for the bushings. You can sign up at the Ibis site linked below for more details as they become available.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.ibiscycles.com/bikes/exie\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>ibiscycles.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b586d8856f81742c4589684f40fd28932941b243d50089669bd13db26cd416c5","category":"Cycling"}